                            Roles and Responsibilities
                            ==========================

Over the last few years (this being now 2004) DW has undegone many changes which have
effected the way that builders right through to supervisors have acted and been treated.
There have been some fairly chaotic years towards the end of the GH era, as well as rapid
advancement of wizards out of necessity during the Acer and now Bammie eras.  You never
know, one day the current old men of DW will have passed on to what ever greener pastures
exist and we may have the Sativa era. (GOD HELP US ALL).

This is the basic procedure outling what can be expected for advancement through the
different wizard ranks as well as to provide an outline or what your responsibilities
are.  The original document came from a list Acer created Jun 04 2002.

One of the things to be aware of is that DW operates on 2 versions. A production version
and a development one. There are different rules for each version which will be addressed
with you at some point. 

                    Roles and Responsibilities of DarkWind Wizzi
                    ============================================

                                   APPLICANT
                                   =========

This is the first phase on the path of becoming a wizard. You have been accepted by a
majority vote of the existing ARCH+ community. You will have your character created on
the development server. The primary function of this role is an interim one for about 3
days to give you the opportunity to read some help files, and decide wether you want to
become a wizard.

When you feel comfortable you will be expected to complete a test. It generally
encompasses 3 basic criteria which you will be expected to maintain during your time as a
builder. These are CODE, CONTENT and LOGIC. 

The test will be conducted by an IMP+, at the time of this writing I conduct the tests. 
You are required to pass all facets to move to the next level. Failure does not mean you
are booted back to being a player (unless of course you want to), you can try the test
again 3 days later.  If you pass the test your character on the development server will
be promoted to the rank of BUILDER.

On the production AKA live server, you will maintain the level of APPLICANT until your
first 30 room area has been connected for player access. 

An applicant MAY NOT walk around the mud. If I catch you playing uno, killing monsters
etc I will personally ban you. You are in this role to take the opportunity to learn what
you need to be a good builder. 

                                    BUILDER
                                    =======

As a BUILDER, your role is exactly that - to build things. Your initial task as a
DarkWind BUILDER is to define, design and develop your own area. You MUST complete this 
before you take on any other tasks. The area must go through the review process. We used
to assign builders old areas to restore, but frankly too many bad habits can be picked up
that way, you may be assigned them after you have been through a Bobreview.

All changes effecting balance in your areas need to be approved by an IMP+, do not
increase gold because you feel like it, or change monster levels, or armour and weapon
quality without having it checked first.

You will be assigned a mentor who is at least of ARCH+ rank, they will answer most of
your questions you have. In the event they are unavailable anyone else will assist you,
but they should still be your first port of call.

As a BUILDER, you have no responsibilities to the players or managing the game. Do not
get involved in the game, players or otherwise. Don't post on boards, don't teleport to
players and talk smack. If you have a problem with players, go invis and just concentrate
on coding.  We have been fairly lax on this ruling of late, but its going to be tightened
up. You can hang in the adventurers guild on live, or in your workroom, but you should
not be wandering around the mud. Virtually everything a BUILDER does sends a message on
the mud security system and WE DO NOT LIKE TO BE SPAMMED. 

If you see something going on that is wrong, please post it on the wiz board, send a
mudmail to the administration, etc..but do not get involved.

We all need to blow of steam everynow and then but generally show respect to those of
higher rank than you. They have done their time which is why they are where they are. 

The builder level can qualify you to have a player character. After much discussion in
December 2003 the following was decided upon to qualify:

  * You must have completed your 30 room area within the time limit. 
  * You must have completed at least 2 additional areas of 125 rooms each i.e. 250
    rooms in total. 
  * All qualifying areas must have passed the review system and problems rectified in
    a timely manner.  And your mentor needs to be satisfied that you deserve a PC.

In addition the following rules exist with the PC:

You MUST remain anonymous to the player base. If one person finds out who you are, the
character will be purged. You are also expected to spend time builder at a ratio of 4:1
so if you spend 1 hour playing, it will need to be accounted for by 4 hours of coding.
Eventually lockouts will be coded for wizard players, and idling as your wizard will be
exempt from the total. Pre-warning you that you ARE still required to build.   

Your PC and your BUILDER character should NEVER be logged on simultaneously. Both will be
banished immediately if this occurs. 

You also have to notify the wizard community of who your character is, in the event we
need you in a hurry to come and fix something. 

You can talk all the smack you like through your PC, just dont do it to other wizards.


To be promoted from BUILDER to ARCHITECT, we require the following milestones:
  * 500+ rooms must be complete
  * 2 guild assignments generally as an assistant to another coder. Writing help docs for
    a guild does NOT count as a guild assignment. 
  * 2 lib assignments that have been given to you by an IMP+
  * 12 months minimum as a BUILDER

The ARCH+ community will review your performance and determine if a promotion is valid.
It is not guaranteed and will be determined by our need for additional ARCH+

                                   ARCHITECT
                                   =========

As a ARCHITECT, your role is to mainly help with guild maintenance - and at times you
will be asked to play a part in lib assignments. You can continue building areas, if you
would like. Or even if you are interested in writing a new guild, please contact an IMP+.
 
Again, you are not responsibile for managing the game. Please defer any possible problems
to IMP+.
 
You may continue to play your Player Character if you want, but you should generally
avoid playing in any guilds that you are either maintaining or working on. We do not want
to see players getting emotional about wizards taking advantage of a mythical power 
curve.


                                  IMPLEMENTOR
                                  ===========

As a IMPLEMENTOR, your role is to do major lib projects and implementations, guilds,
areas, everything basically. :) You ARE responsible for the game, how it is run, and
monitoring and enforcing the rules.
 
To make IMPLEMENTOR, we require the following milestones as well as any preceeding
requirements that have not been previously met:

  * 1 real year of maintaining a production Guild
  * 2 major guild projects or implementations AND/OR writing a new guild
  * 5 lib assignments AND/OR 2 major lib projects or implementations
  * 2+ real years of service as a wiz
  * In-depth knowledge of the game. Mechanics, playability, and otherwise.
  * A desire to idle is also appreciated in this role.
 
  
                                  SUPERVISOR
                                  ==========

As a SUPERVISOR, your role is to do major lib projets and implementations, guilds, 
areas, as well as managing the organization, roles and responsiblities, training, 
etc... but the main role is to be the leadership of the MUD, helping to steer it's 
direction.
 
To make SUPERVISOR, it's a case-by-case basis to be made by the other SUPERVISORs. 
As a SUPERVISOR, you are considered an owner of DarkWind, and as such, are
expected to act like one in all regards.
 
You are also required to idle extensively.
 
--------------------------------
 
Again, take these to heart and you'll quickly find yourself a key member of 
DarkWind's wizardhood - fight these, and you'll find yourself back on the streets
of DarkWind, just another player again.
 
Be proud of being a DarkWind wizard! And, remember, what you do reflects the
wizardhood as a whole! So, always act with professionalism and integrity.
 
If you have any questions, feel free to ask myself or any other IMP+.


